{"questionId":"15593","questionHtml":"<p>Find the equation of the tangent line to the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 2\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;Give the equation in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"ax + by + d = 0\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> where,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>, and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d \\in \\mathbb{Z}\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{8}{3} = 6\\left( 2 \\right) + c\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>8</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for 2, their part (a) and their part (e) substituted into equation of a straight line.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c =&nbsp; - \\frac{{28}}{3}\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {y - \\frac{8}{3}} \\right) = 6\\left( {x - 2} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>8</mn>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;for 2, their part (a) and their part (e) substituted into equation of a straight line.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 6x - \\frac{{28}}{3}\\,\\,\\left( {y = 6x - 9.33333 \\ldots } \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>6</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>9.33333</mn>\n      <mo>…</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;for&nbsp;their answer to (e) and intercept&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\frac{{28}}{3}\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>28</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;substituted in the gradient-intercept line equation.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 18x + 3y + 28 = 0\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>18</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>28</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;(accept integer multiples)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)</strong><strong><em>(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from parts (a) and (e).</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15593","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.T_5f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of the tangent line to the graph of y = f ( x ) at x = 2 . Give the equation in the form a x + b y + d = 0 where, a , b , and d ∈ Z .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.1—Introduction of differential calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}